nsidered. The l1 norm is the most\nrobust of all considered metrics, because being linear it is less sensitive to\nimage smoothing by high regularisation levels. For the cases considered, this\nmetric allows the implementation of automatic quality assessment of\nreconstructed images, with a performance similar to human selection.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Nov 2016 16:58:28 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 20 Feb 2017 22:12:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-22"}
